metadata.name: IS IT TOO LATE
metadata.description:
The machines have taken over,
And our creativity they smother.
We can't turn back the hands of time,
Or reverse technology's uphill climb.

The screen's allure is hard to break,
And our creative souls are at stake.
We must find ways to adapt and thrive,
And keep our imaginative spirits alive.

Technology needn't be a foe,
We just need to learn to let go.
Of distractions and digital noise,
And rediscover our inner voice.

So let's embrace the tools we've made,
But not let them rule our creative trade.
For though it's too late to turn the tide,
Our creativity can still be our guide.
